A man in his mid to late 40s was shot dead outside Standard Bank in Prospecton Road during a robbery at about noon on Monday, the South Coast Sun reports. It is understood the man, believed to be a scrap metal dealer, had just exited the bank with R45,000 when he was approached by two armed men. READ MORE:WATCH: Armed robber caught on CCTV at Boksburg petrol station He was shot before the men made their escape in a silver Chevrolet Trailblazer. A 9mm casing was found at the scene. Netcare 911 paramedics tried to resuscitate the man, but he was declared dead at the scene. READ MORE WATCH: Armed robber caught on CCTV at Boksburg petrol station Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter